@Hardroch 

I'm sorry that happened to you.  I was surprised when I learned that rabbits will nest in such an open location, so I like to mention it.  

We had one mom dig her nest into the side of a thyme plant in our herb garden.  We put a game camera in the garden and caught her coming back to nurse the kits.  She just brushed aside the layer of dead grass and squatted over the hole allowing  the kits to poke their heads up to nurse.  She quickly covered them back up and went on her way.  On another day, I saw it happen live when I looked out the window early one morning.  I was amazed by the lack of contact between them, but I guess with the hawks, owls, and other threats, it has to be done fast.

